received an associate of arts from waldorf college and a bachelors degree from the university of denver in  anderson joined sound of music a small chain of stereo stores that were the precursor to best buy as a commissioned salesman it took him two weeks to make his first sale best buyfounder richard schulze named him vice president in  where anderson operated as the founders righthand man in the subsequent years schulze and anderson turned the chain from a commissiondriven store to a discount store warehousestyle format in  anderson was promoted to executive vice president and was elected to best buy’s board of directors in april  he was promoted to president and chief operating officer vice chairman in  and in june  he assumed the position of chief executive officer in june  he was succeeded by brian j dunn who was serving as president and chief operating officer anderson serves on the waldorf college board of regents and the general mills board of directors referencesedit  carissa wyant and tom smith best buys ceo paid  million archived december   at the wayback machine minneapolis  st paul business journal may    carissa wyant best buy ceo salary flat yearoveryear archived december   at the wayback machine minneapolis  st paul business journal april    matthew boyle best buys giant gamble archived september   at the wayback machine fortune magazine march    matthew boyle qa with best buy ceo brad anderson archived february   at the wayback machine fortune magazine april    christine persaud best buy ceo to retire brian dunn named successor marketnews january   biography at best buy website business positions preceded by richard m schulze best buy ceo – succeeded by brian j dunn this article about an american businessperson born in the s is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlebradandersonexecutiveoldid categories american retail chief executivesliving people birthsuniversity of denver alumniamerican 